<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-0931 </DOCNO><TEXT>It is found that dual drives of belt conveyors have to be laid out consideringcertain constraints of operational conditions, e.g., under steady-stateoperation, starting and braking conditions, etc. In general, load isshared between the two motors in the same ratio as their rated horse-powers,provided their torque-speed characteristics are exactly similar and theoperation is at steady-state. Otherwise, load sharing may be quite different,especially under transient conditions like starting and braking.</TEXT></DOC>